                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13536226" author="yukim" created="Wed, 19 Dec 2012 18:16:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch attached to calculate ownership using BigInteger/BigDecimal for range (Long.MIN_VALUE, Long.MAX_VALUE].&lt;br/&gt;
This will also resolve problem described in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4598&quot; title=&quot;describeOwnership() in Murmur3Partitioner.java doesn&amp;#39;t work for close tokens&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-4598&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-4598&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13536260" author="slebresne" created="Wed, 19 Dec 2012 18:34:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For the last range, I think the &lt;tt&gt;ti.subtract(tim1)&lt;/tt&gt; part should be changed to &lt;tt&gt;(BigIntegerToken)start).token.subtract(ti)&lt;/tt&gt; as done in RandomPartitionner.describeOwnership. Cause at the end of the loop, &lt;tt&gt;ti == tim1&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But +1 with that fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13536281" author="yukim" created="Wed, 19 Dec 2012 18:44:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed with fix for review. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
